{"sha": "7612ad77975331c91aec8ab2a269b31b22668972", "node_id": "MDY6Q29tbWl0NzI0NzEyOjc2MTJhZDc3OTc1MzMxYzkxYWVjOGFiMmEyNjliMzFiMjI2Njg5NzI=", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Ulrik Sverdrup", "email": "bluss@users.noreply.github.com", "date": "2020-04-14T19:35:37Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Ulrik Sverdrup", "email": "bluss@users.noreply.github.com", "date": "2020-04-14T19:51:48Z"}, "message": "Vec drop and truncate: drop using raw slice *mut [T]\n\nBy creating a *mut [T] directly (without going through &mut [T]), avoid\nquestions of validity of the contents of the slice.\n\nConsider the following risky code:\n\n```rust\nunsafe {\n    let mut v = Vec::<bool>::with_capacity(16);\n    v.set_len(16);\n}\n```\n\nThe intention is that with this change, the above snippet will be\nsound because Vec::drop does no longer produces a mutable slice of\nthe vector's contents.", "tree": {"sha": "c4c4b7f023a65c6617e31dc4bcda948d7a9fb912", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/trees/c4c4b7f023a65c6617e31dc4bcda948d7a9fb912"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/commits/7612ad77975331c91aec8ab2a269b31b22668972", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/7612ad77975331c91aec8ab2a269b31b22668972", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/7612ad77975331c91aec8ab2a269b31b22668972", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/7612ad77975331c91aec8ab2a269b31b22668972/comments", "author": {"login": "bluss", "id": 3209739, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMyMDk3Mzk=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3209739?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluss", "html_url": "https://github.com/bluss", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluss/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluss/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https: